1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:22,001
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:37,605 --> 00:00:40,305
[This drama is fictional and any similarity
with reality is purely coincidental.]

3
00:00:40,305 --> 00:00:42,672
[Production guidelines were followed
when filming children and animals.]

4
00:00:42,672 --> 00:00:46,272
She is really precious to me.

5
00:00:46,272 --> 00:00:49,172
[Episode 10]
So I can't lie to deny her.

6
00:00:49,172 --> 00:00:52,872
It's okay if you doubt me and criticize me.

7
00:00:52,872 --> 00:00:57,138
But please refrain from excessive criticism

8
00:00:58,138 --> 00:01:00,905
or speculation about them.

9
00:01:00,905 --> 00:01:03,238
I sincerely request this.

10
00:01:21,445 --> 00:01:24,869
According to him, they are actually in love.

11
00:01:44,338 --> 00:01:46,638
Why did you do that?

12
00:01:46,638 --> 00:01:48,705
I told you to hide it.

13
00:01:49,472 --> 00:01:50,572
I'm sorry.

14
00:01:50,572 --> 00:01:53,638
But even if I went back,

15
00:01:53,638 --> 00:01:56,405
I probably would do the same.

16
00:01:56,405 --> 00:02:00,572
I don't want to act as if you
and our Yeol Mu never happened.

17
00:02:41,372 --> 00:02:42,705
This is my choice too.

18
00:02:42,705 --> 00:02:44,872
I knew it wouldn't be easy when I started,

19
00:02:44,872 --> 00:02:47,905
so rather than regretting that choice,

20
00:02:47,905 --> 00:02:50,805
I want to do my best in whatever I can do.

21
00:02:50,805 --> 00:02:52,272
Thanks for worrying about me.

22
00:02:52,272 --> 00:02:53,272
I'll get through this.

23
00:02:53,272 --> 00:02:56,072
You know I'm strong in a crisis.

24
00:03:19,405 --> 00:03:20,972
I watched the press conference.

25
00:03:20,972 --> 00:03:22,238
I thought you were impressive,

26
00:03:22,238 --> 00:03:24,205
even as a man.

27
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:28,538
Anyone would do that
to protect someone they care about.

28
00:03:28,538 --> 00:03:29,538
Is that so?

29
00:03:29,538 --> 00:03:31,072
It seems that stubborn Hui Won

30
00:03:31,072 --> 00:03:34,872
needs someone like you
who could bear all that.

31
00:03:34,872 --> 00:03:37,093
Someone who can protect her

32
00:03:37,093 --> 00:03:38,905
in any situation.

33
00:03:43,877 --> 00:03:47,205
Please take good care of Hui Won.

34
00:04:04,372 --> 00:04:06,038
[The greatest romantic of our time]
President Kang Du Jun,

35
00:04:06,038 --> 00:04:08,138
ascends as the greatest romantic of our time.

36
00:04:08,138 --> 00:04:09,338
The way this man loves.

37
00:04:09,338 --> 00:04:11,805
[The way he loves, I'll take the criticism]
I will take the criticism.

38
00:04:11,805 --> 00:04:13,238
Even as a man, I admit it.

39
00:04:13,238 --> 00:04:14,405
I was really surprised.

40
00:04:14,405 --> 00:04:16,038
Instead of an explanation,
he actually confessed.

41
00:04:16,038 --> 00:04:17,405
As expected of the President.

42
00:04:17,405 --> 00:04:19,438
The video views totally exploded too.

43
00:04:19,438 --> 00:04:22,272
When I checked this morning,
the public opinion seems to have swung,

44
00:04:22,272 --> 00:04:23,938
and the stock has recovered a lot.

45
00:04:23,938 --> 00:04:27,438
Honestly, isn't this basically
like proposing,

46
00:04:27,438 --> 00:04:30,005
saying 'I love you'
in front of the whole country?

47
00:04:30,005 --> 00:04:31,538
When will I ever get a proposal like that?

48
00:04:31,538 --> 00:04:33,272
Try hinting at it to your boyfriend.

49
00:04:33,272 --> 00:04:34,305
We broke up.

50
00:04:34,305 --> 00:04:35,572
- Again?
- Again?

51
00:04:35,572 --> 00:04:37,205
Wasn't this supposed
to be true love this time?

52
00:04:37,205 --> 00:04:38,538
It wasn't true love.

53
00:04:38,538 --> 00:04:40,338
It was triple love, triple love.

54
00:04:40,338 --> 00:04:43,605
I thought he was a caring,
warm-hearted person.

55
00:04:43,605 --> 00:04:46,738
But he was taking care of his ex
and even his ex-ex.

56
00:04:46,738 --> 00:04:48,072
Oh, Manager Jang.

57
00:04:48,072 --> 00:04:49,405
Sit here for a moment.

58
00:04:49,405 --> 00:04:51,238
Manager, did you see
yesterday's press conference?

59
00:04:51,238 --> 00:04:52,838
I want to be his number one fan.

60
00:04:52,838 --> 00:04:55,372
Ah, I had some business yesterday, so...

61
00:04:55,372 --> 00:04:58,117
The President must have
been really impressive.

62
00:04:58,117 --> 00:05:01,772
Who on earth is the woman
the President is seeing?

63
00:05:01,772 --> 00:05:02,872
I'm jealous.

64
00:05:02,872 --> 00:05:05,005
She must have saved
the country in her past life.

65
00:05:05,005 --> 00:05:06,538
Just the country?

66
00:05:06,538 --> 00:05:07,938
She probably saved the whole world.

67
00:05:07,938 --> 00:05:11,038
I think that person must be
just as impressive as the President.

68
00:05:11,038 --> 00:05:12,438
Se Hyeon, do you know something?

69
00:05:12,438 --> 00:05:13,805
You talk like you've met her.

70
00:05:13,805 --> 00:05:15,738
Oh, come on, do you
have to see someone to know?

71
00:05:15,738 --> 00:05:17,957
Just the look in the President's eyes,
the tremor in his voice

72
00:05:17,957 --> 00:05:19,005
when he talks about her.

73
00:05:19,005 --> 00:05:21,272
It tells you everything.

74
00:05:23,705 --> 00:05:25,772
The President being impressive is one thing,

75
00:05:25,772 --> 00:05:27,772
but we also have to work impressively.

76
00:05:27,772 --> 00:05:29,972
To the conference room in 10 minutes.

77
00:05:29,972 --> 00:05:32,338
Understood.

78
00:05:37,705 --> 00:05:39,365
[President Kang Du Jun ascends
as the greatest romantic of our time]

79
00:05:44,372 --> 00:05:47,705
I think our team is forming
a Kang Du Jun fan club.

80
00:05:47,705 --> 00:05:50,905
Seems like you are not just
impressive to my eyes.

81
00:05:50,905 --> 00:05:53,072
I think so too.

82
00:05:58,505 --> 00:06:00,205
Yes.

83
00:06:08,205 --> 00:06:09,505
It's not over yet.

84
00:06:09,505 --> 00:06:10,905
The real beginning starts now.

85
00:06:10,905 --> 00:06:14,205
Even if public opinion has turned,
it wasn't an action worthy of praise.

86
00:06:14,205 --> 00:06:15,638
It was a risky move.

87
00:06:15,638 --> 00:06:18,005
The stock price hasn't
fully recovered yet either.

88
00:06:18,005 --> 00:06:19,205
I know.

89
00:06:19,205 --> 00:06:22,072
I will take responsibility
until the damages are fully restored.

90
00:06:22,072 --> 00:06:24,572
You'll need to pay even more
attention going forward.

91
00:06:24,572 --> 00:06:27,638
Still, it falls far short of
the qualifications of a true entrepreneur.

92
00:06:27,638 --> 00:06:31,505
But in terms of making the company
approachable to the public,

93
00:06:31,505 --> 00:06:33,105
it wasn't a bad choice.

94
00:06:33,105 --> 00:06:36,305
After all, a company is made up of people.

95
00:06:36,972 --> 00:06:39,472
Her name is Jang Hui Won, right?

96
00:06:39,472 --> 00:06:40,505
Father, how did you...

97
00:06:40,505 --> 00:06:42,172
She's the woman you're
so determined to protect.

98
00:06:42,172 --> 00:06:43,405
Go arrange it.

99
00:06:43,405 --> 00:06:45,538
Let's have a meal together.

100
00:06:46,705 --> 00:06:48,405
Yes.

101
00:06:55,672 --> 00:06:57,472
What happened?

102
00:06:57,472 --> 00:06:59,305
The thing you did to wreck his image

103
00:06:59,305 --> 00:07:02,805
ended up making him likable!

104
00:07:02,805 --> 00:07:03,872
What are you going to do now?

105
00:07:03,872 --> 00:07:05,138
Do you have a backup plan?

106
00:07:05,138 --> 00:07:08,772
How many times do I
have to spell it out for you?

107
00:07:09,472 --> 00:07:13,072
If you're so anxious and dissatisfied,
just step away from this.

108
00:07:13,072 --> 00:07:15,605
I don't care either way.

109
00:07:15,605 --> 00:07:18,872
No, I'm just concerned.

110
00:07:18,872 --> 00:07:22,205
I told you there's a plan B.

111
00:07:22,205 --> 00:07:25,872
Kang Du Jun has been
on psychiatric medication for over ten years.

112
00:07:25,872 --> 00:07:29,705
Yet he still can't shake hands
during external meetings

113
00:07:29,705 --> 00:07:32,438
or over important contracts.

114
00:07:32,438 --> 00:07:37,638
Instead of coming here constantly,
why not manage the board members?

115
00:07:37,638 --> 00:07:38,872
Can you handle that?

116
00:07:38,872 --> 00:07:40,872
Yes, of course.

117
00:07:40,872 --> 00:07:43,405
I'll take care of the board.

118
00:07:43,405 --> 00:07:46,738
Of course, I'll take care of it.

119
00:07:59,269 --> 00:08:01,893
[Han Jeong Eum]

120
00:08:24,572 --> 00:08:26,505
No.

121
00:08:30,705 --> 00:08:32,272
No, baby.

122
00:08:32,272 --> 00:08:34,172
No.

123
00:08:35,372 --> 00:08:38,305
Baby, no.

124
00:08:41,765 --> 00:08:43,845
[Han Jeong Eum]

125
00:08:56,613 --> 00:08:57,861
[Non-alcoholic beer is evolving
into a new beverage category]

126
00:09:00,405 --> 00:09:02,338
Manager Jang, working late again today?

127
00:09:02,338 --> 00:09:04,038
Because of that contest?

128
00:09:04,038 --> 00:09:08,672
Yes, I had a sudden idea,
so I'll wrap this up before leaving.

129
00:09:08,672 --> 00:09:12,305
Hey, working this hard alone
makes me feel guilty as a teammate.

130
00:09:12,305 --> 00:09:14,172
I'm doing it because I enjoy it.

131
00:09:14,172 --> 00:09:15,372
I'll share everything anyway.

132
00:09:15,372 --> 00:09:16,572
Then let's work together.

133
00:09:16,572 --> 00:09:18,238
It'll finish quickly together.

134
00:09:18,238 --> 00:09:20,305
Ah, no.

135
00:09:20,305 --> 00:09:22,405
I'll finish this quickly
and head home soon too.

136
00:09:22,405 --> 00:09:23,505
So go ahead.

137
00:09:23,505 --> 00:09:26,005
It's fine, you go first.

138
00:09:26,005 --> 00:09:27,272
Make sure to share it, okay?

139
00:09:27,272 --> 00:09:29,605
Youngest managers aren't made overnight.

140
00:09:29,605 --> 00:09:30,917
See you tomorrow.

141
00:09:30,917 --> 00:09:33,172
Wow, I feel ashamed.

142
00:09:33,172 --> 00:09:34,705
What?

143
00:09:34,705 --> 00:09:36,505
- Still...
- It's okay.

144
00:09:36,505 --> 00:09:38,372
Go quickly.

145
00:09:38,372 --> 00:09:39,605
Then, fighting!

146
00:09:39,605 --> 00:09:41,105
- Fighting!
- See you tomorrow.

147
00:09:41,105 --> 00:09:43,372
Yeah, see you tomorrow.

148
00:09:51,238 --> 00:09:52,837
[Non-alcoholic beer is evolving
into a new beverage category]

149
00:09:58,472 --> 00:10:00,605
Is she very busy?

150
00:10:08,705 --> 00:10:10,272
You're probably crazy to see her, huh?

151
00:10:10,272 --> 00:10:12,805
You scared me, jeez.

152
00:10:12,805 --> 00:10:14,838
Why are you here?

153
00:10:16,572 --> 00:10:17,572
Team Leader Bang?

154
00:10:17,572 --> 00:10:19,205
Who else would I come to see?

155
00:10:19,205 --> 00:10:22,472
Team Leader Bang is a charming woman.

156
00:10:24,372 --> 00:10:25,605
Hey, how did you know?

157
00:10:25,605 --> 00:10:28,638
I know you inside out.

158
00:10:28,638 --> 00:10:31,638
If you're dating, why can't you just say it?

159
00:10:32,405 --> 00:10:34,772
Then I'll head out first.

160
00:10:34,772 --> 00:10:35,972
How dare you leave before me?

161
00:10:35,972 --> 00:10:37,505
I haven't even left work yet.

162
00:10:37,505 --> 00:10:40,705
Si Hyeong, please go buy
some late-night snacks for Hui Won.

163
00:10:40,705 --> 00:10:42,605
- Hey!
- For Team Leader Bang too.

164
00:10:42,605 --> 00:10:44,538
What would they like, both of them?

165
00:10:44,538 --> 00:10:46,272
Card, card!

166
00:10:47,538 --> 00:10:50,938
You're really gonna be rich, huh?

167
00:10:50,938 --> 00:10:52,672
Buy a lot.

168
00:11:00,105 --> 00:11:01,872
[Global &amp; domestic non-alcoholic beer market]
Manager.

169
00:11:03,238 --> 00:11:04,272
Se Hyeon too.

170
00:11:04,272 --> 00:11:05,505
Wow, Manager Jang.

171
00:11:05,505 --> 00:11:07,772
Seeing it again,
non-alcoholic is really nice.

172
00:11:07,772 --> 00:11:09,072
- Really?
- Yeah.

173
00:11:09,072 --> 00:11:10,438
When did you do all this?

174
00:11:10,438 --> 00:11:12,638
Manager, this is incredible.

175
00:11:12,638 --> 00:11:14,138
You're not complimenting me
for no reason, right?

176
00:11:14,138 --> 00:11:17,238
No, no. Our team is a complete dream team.

177
00:11:17,238 --> 00:11:20,505
If you're free this weekend,
let's meet my parents.

178
00:11:20,505 --> 00:11:23,938
I've got a family, so I can't join you,
which is such a shame.

179
00:11:23,938 --> 00:11:26,085
How did you manage this?

180
00:11:26,085 --> 00:11:28,472
Huh?

181
00:11:28,472 --> 00:11:30,405
President.

182
00:11:32,805 --> 00:11:35,538
Please sit, please sit.

183
00:11:38,597 --> 00:11:40,549
Oh.

184
00:11:54,053 --> 00:11:55,109
[Flavor stabilization,
reduced astringent aftertaste]

185
00:12:09,838 --> 00:12:11,013
[The new value of non-alcoholic beer]

186
00:12:19,705 --> 00:12:20,738
Good morning.

187
00:12:20,738 --> 00:12:22,105
Yes, good morning.

188
00:12:22,105 --> 00:12:24,638
Manager Jang. Did you come early?
Or pull an all-nighter?

189
00:12:24,638 --> 00:12:25,705
It's a secret.

190
00:12:25,705 --> 00:12:28,638
Ah, Manager. Have some coffee.

191
00:12:28,638 --> 00:12:29,705
Thank you.

192
00:12:29,705 --> 00:12:31,372
Can I drink this instead?

193
00:12:31,372 --> 00:12:32,538
- Sure.
- I'll enjoy it.

194
00:12:32,538 --> 00:12:34,172
Hello.

195
00:12:34,172 --> 00:12:35,172
- Yes.
- Hi.

196
00:12:35,172 --> 00:12:36,338
Assistant Manager Choi, hair roller.

197
00:12:36,338 --> 00:12:38,172
- Want to borrow it?
- No, It's fine.

198
00:12:38,172 --> 00:12:39,872
- Tak Soo.
- Yes.

199
00:12:42,238 --> 00:12:45,538
Make sure to eat lunch while working.

200
00:12:45,538 --> 00:12:49,505
Working hard is good,
but think about me sometimes too.

201
00:12:55,705 --> 00:12:57,572
Thank you.

202
00:13:11,705 --> 00:13:14,405
But is it really this hard
to go on a date once?

203
00:13:14,405 --> 00:13:16,205
There isn't much time left
to submit the contest.

204
00:13:16,205 --> 00:13:17,205
Please bear with me for a few days.

205
00:13:17,205 --> 00:13:19,705
I know you're more ambitious than anyone.

206
00:13:19,705 --> 00:13:23,605
But I'm worried you might
get sick from overworking.

207
00:13:23,605 --> 00:13:26,438
I didn't plan to push this far.

208
00:13:26,438 --> 00:13:29,338
But as I prepared, I became ambitious.

209
00:13:29,338 --> 00:13:31,405
After giving up studying in Germany,

210
00:13:31,405 --> 00:13:33,438
I wondered when I'd get
another chance like this.

211
00:13:33,438 --> 00:13:35,272
I thought maybe this contest

212
00:13:35,272 --> 00:13:37,105
could be that chance.

213
00:13:37,105 --> 00:13:41,138
A brand bearing my name, the next Try Beer.

214
00:13:41,138 --> 00:13:43,429
Just thinking about it makes me excited.

215
00:13:43,429 --> 00:13:46,905
Oh, it's not like I'm asking
for special treatment for no reason.

216
00:13:46,905 --> 00:13:49,438
Don't misunderstand.

217
00:13:49,438 --> 00:13:52,205
I was planning to step out of judging anyway.

218
00:13:52,205 --> 00:13:54,472
If our relationship gets out later,

219
00:13:54,472 --> 00:13:56,872
it could cause unnecessary gossip.

220
00:13:56,872 --> 00:14:00,572
So for this contest, just do everything
you want to do without holding back.

221
00:14:00,572 --> 00:14:02,272
Okay.

222
00:14:04,038 --> 00:14:07,205
Oh, and by the way,
are you free this weekend?

223
00:14:07,205 --> 00:14:11,365
My parents suggested
we have a casual meal together.

224
00:14:11,365 --> 00:14:12,772
Oh.

225
00:14:12,772 --> 00:14:14,805
If you feel pressured, you can decline.

226
00:14:14,805 --> 00:14:16,905
We can do it another time
when we have the chance.

227
00:14:16,905 --> 00:14:18,105
Sounds good.

228
00:14:18,105 --> 00:14:19,638
They'd probably be curious.

229
00:14:19,638 --> 00:14:20,838
Please set it up.

230
00:14:20,838 --> 00:14:23,172
I'll properly introduce myself to them.

231
00:14:27,872 --> 00:14:29,705
Is this too conservative?

232
00:14:29,705 --> 00:14:32,005
Or maybe too drab?

233
00:14:32,005 --> 00:14:33,672
Then this one...

234
00:14:33,672 --> 00:14:36,105
Hey, Jang Hui Won.

235
00:14:36,105 --> 00:14:37,372
I knew you'd be like this.

236
00:14:37,372 --> 00:14:39,505
You still haven't picked your outfit?

237
00:14:40,405 --> 00:14:41,438
Look.

238
00:14:41,438 --> 00:14:44,438
Is this better? Or this one?

239
00:14:44,438 --> 00:14:47,238
I guess I should skip tight clothes
now that my belly's showing more, right?

240
00:14:47,238 --> 00:14:51,238
You're wearing this
to meet your future in-laws?

241
00:14:51,238 --> 00:14:53,338
I must have been out of my mind then.

242
00:14:53,338 --> 00:14:56,261
Why did I agree to go?

243
00:14:56,261 --> 00:14:58,538
Look at this one.

244
00:14:58,538 --> 00:15:01,372
How about this dress?

245
00:15:02,672 --> 00:15:04,738
- Stylish, right?
- Not at all.

246
00:15:04,738 --> 00:15:05,772
Absolutely not.

247
00:15:05,772 --> 00:15:08,438
Take that off and follow me.

248
00:15:10,872 --> 00:15:13,672
Hey, wait!

249
00:15:18,138 --> 00:15:19,272
Hello, Director.

250
00:15:19,272 --> 00:15:20,305
- Hello.
- Hello.

251
00:15:20,305 --> 00:15:23,738
Today, my friend must
look elegant yet graceful,

252
00:15:23,738 --> 00:15:25,405
clear yet vivid,

253
00:15:25,405 --> 00:15:26,661
and finally with a touch of lovely,
juicy charm.

254
00:15:26,661 --> 00:15:28,869
You know what I mean, right?

255
00:15:29,872 --> 00:15:31,172
Isn't that too much?

256
00:15:31,172 --> 00:15:35,605
Do you know how many couples
got married after just one touch from her?

257
00:15:35,605 --> 00:15:38,905
Please start. I'm counting on you.

258
00:15:58,438 --> 00:16:01,305
Carry my bag. I'm so nervous.

259
00:16:26,738 --> 00:16:28,305
You've waited long, haven't you?

260
00:16:28,305 --> 00:16:30,005
Shall we go?

261
00:16:31,872 --> 00:16:32,972
Why?

262
00:16:32,972 --> 00:16:35,638
Is it too much after all?

263
00:16:36,338 --> 00:16:37,638
You look so beautiful.

264
00:16:37,638 --> 00:16:39,638
You've always been this beautiful.

265
00:16:39,638 --> 00:16:43,438
But if you keep getting prettier every day,
how am I supposed to handle it?

266
00:16:43,438 --> 00:16:44,572
Ah, you're exaggerating.

267
00:16:44,572 --> 00:16:46,505
I don't know. Let's hurry.

268
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:48,738
No, not exaggeration.
I'm speaking from the heart.

269
00:16:48,738 --> 00:16:51,105
Hurry up. They're waiting.

270
00:16:51,105 --> 00:16:52,605
But aren't you nervous at all?

271
00:16:52,605 --> 00:16:55,538
I'm nervous. I'm shaking like crazy. Come on.

272
00:16:55,538 --> 00:16:57,605
Why are you so nervous?

273
00:16:59,505 --> 00:17:02,205
Was the trip here difficult?

274
00:17:02,205 --> 00:17:03,472
And are you feeling okay physically?

275
00:17:03,472 --> 00:17:05,272
Yes, I'm fine.

276
00:17:05,272 --> 00:17:07,338
Thank you for your concern.

277
00:17:07,338 --> 00:17:10,705
I felt a bit uneasy
sending you off like that last time.

278
00:17:10,705 --> 00:17:14,205
Please take it as meddling
from parents who lost a child.

279
00:17:14,205 --> 00:17:15,405
Not at all.

280
00:17:15,405 --> 00:17:16,772
I completely understand.

281
00:17:16,772 --> 00:17:17,772
What do you mean, last time?

282
00:17:17,772 --> 00:17:19,905
Father, have you met Hui Won before?

283
00:17:19,905 --> 00:17:23,338
Only she and I know about this secret.

284
00:17:23,338 --> 00:17:25,505
You don't need to know.

285
00:17:25,505 --> 00:17:28,205
How can that be? You didn't even tell me.

286
00:17:28,205 --> 00:17:32,938
Anyway, since you're pregnant,
shouldn't you take a break from work?

287
00:17:32,938 --> 00:17:35,505
- Pardon?
- Hui Won is exceptionally capable.

288
00:17:35,505 --> 00:17:36,738
So she has a lot on her plate.

289
00:17:36,738 --> 00:17:39,238
Did I ask you?

290
00:17:39,238 --> 00:17:43,772
I'm worried it might be hard
since she's carrying a child.

291
00:17:43,772 --> 00:17:46,305
Does the company know about the pregnancy?

292
00:17:46,305 --> 00:17:47,805
We want to take it slow on that.

293
00:17:47,805 --> 00:17:49,605
They don't know yet.

294
00:17:49,605 --> 00:17:50,605
Why not?

295
00:17:50,605 --> 00:17:53,472
Is there some reason you can't reveal it?

296
00:17:53,472 --> 00:17:56,138
Does she need a reason?

297
00:17:56,138 --> 00:17:59,005
It's probably because
their relationship is still a secret.

298
00:17:59,005 --> 00:18:01,972
I'm just asking because I'm curious.

299
00:18:01,972 --> 00:18:05,238
Because I know nothing about this young lady.

300
00:18:06,072 --> 00:18:09,505
Given the nature of our work, pregnant
employees often get reduced workloads.

301
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:11,805
Or get removed from projects.

302
00:18:11,805 --> 00:18:13,505
Even when stepping back,

303
00:18:13,505 --> 00:18:15,972
I want to wrap things up as much as possible.

304
00:18:15,972 --> 00:18:19,005
This is all out of consideration
for the team.

305
00:18:24,105 --> 00:18:25,805
I'm sorry.

306
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:29,572
Excuse me, it's a bit chilly in here.

307
00:18:29,572 --> 00:18:31,505
Could you raise the temperature?

308
00:18:31,505 --> 00:18:33,638
Yes, one moment.

309
00:18:39,813 --> 00:18:41,572
Um, here.

310
00:18:41,572 --> 00:18:43,438
Alright.

311
00:18:43,438 --> 00:18:45,038
Thank you.

312
00:18:45,038 --> 00:18:46,538
I was a bit cold.

313
00:18:46,538 --> 00:18:48,938
Actually, I was cold too.

314
00:18:48,938 --> 00:18:52,738
Thanks to you, it feels
so warm and comfortable.

315
00:18:52,738 --> 00:18:53,738
Okay, let's dig in.

316
00:18:53,738 --> 00:18:56,972
Yes, I'll enjoy it.

317
00:19:00,872 --> 00:19:02,172
Was it tiring today?

318
00:19:02,172 --> 00:19:04,705
It was fun. They were both really nice.

319
00:19:04,705 --> 00:19:07,905
I apologize for my mom
being irritable earlier.

320
00:19:07,905 --> 00:19:09,738
She's not normally like that, but today...

321
00:19:09,738 --> 00:19:13,005
It's because she cares about you so much.

322
00:19:13,005 --> 00:19:16,338
She wants her son to be with a good woman.
That's why she acts that way.

323
00:19:16,338 --> 00:19:18,738
Where else can I find a woman as good as you?

324
00:19:18,738 --> 00:19:21,405
And my mom too...

325
00:19:21,405 --> 00:19:23,872
I'm jealous. Your family seems so warm.

326
00:19:23,872 --> 00:19:26,272
Your family is nice,

327
00:19:26,272 --> 00:19:27,512
but I don't have a father,

328
00:19:27,512 --> 00:19:29,538
and my relationship with my mom is strained.

329
00:19:29,538 --> 00:19:31,405
Of course, she wouldn't like me.

330
00:19:31,405 --> 00:19:33,005
Not like you? Who wouldn't?

331
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:34,472
My mom would never think that way.

332
00:19:34,472 --> 00:19:35,505
Don't misunderstand that.

333
00:19:35,505 --> 00:19:38,772
Besides, in this day and age,
divorce happens,

334
00:19:38,772 --> 00:19:40,172
and mothers and daughters argue sometimes.

335
00:19:40,172 --> 00:19:44,572
If anyone says anything about that,
bring them to me. I'll teach them a lesson.

336
00:19:48,838 --> 00:19:49,972
And

337
00:19:49,972 --> 00:19:53,238
your mother must have
acted out of deep affection.

338
00:19:53,238 --> 00:19:56,072
She really cares about you.

339
00:19:56,072 --> 00:19:58,205
It's just a different way of showing it.

340
00:19:58,205 --> 00:20:00,238
How do you know that, President?

341
00:20:00,238 --> 00:20:02,138
My mom isn't like that at all, okay?

342
00:20:02,138 --> 00:20:04,138
What if I'm right about this?

343
00:20:07,272 --> 00:20:11,172
I'm sorry to visit unannounced,
but I felt it was the right thing to do.

344
00:20:11,172 --> 00:20:13,638
With all the commotion online,

345
00:20:13,638 --> 00:20:15,738
it's impossible to ignore.

346
00:20:15,738 --> 00:20:18,972
I sincerely apologize for causing concern.

347
00:20:18,972 --> 00:20:19,972
I saw it well.

348
00:20:19,972 --> 00:20:21,772
Thank you

349
00:20:23,272 --> 00:20:26,205
for keeping your word back then.

350
00:20:26,205 --> 00:20:28,872
I hope Hui Won

351
00:20:28,872 --> 00:20:30,638
doesn't live

352
00:20:31,905 --> 00:20:34,305
like I did.

353
00:20:37,672 --> 00:20:39,372
So

354
00:20:40,205 --> 00:20:42,438
keep that promise.

355
00:20:43,205 --> 00:20:45,805
I'll be watching for now.

356
00:20:50,038 --> 00:20:51,905
Okay.

357
00:21:07,838 --> 00:21:11,305
Your mother must have
acted out of deep affection.

358
00:21:11,305 --> 00:21:14,138
She really cares about you.

359
00:21:23,438 --> 00:21:25,541
[Mom]

360
00:21:31,005 --> 00:21:32,165
[Mom]

361
00:21:42,505 --> 00:21:45,405
How was your meeting with
your future daughter-in-law?

362
00:21:47,605 --> 00:21:50,138
What a shame. Invite me
to the formal meeting too.

363
00:21:50,138 --> 00:21:52,105
We're family after all.

364
00:21:53,072 --> 00:21:56,072
What brings you here unannounced?

365
00:21:57,105 --> 00:21:58,672
I believe the time has come.

366
00:21:58,672 --> 00:22:01,872
You remember what I said before, right?

367
00:22:01,872 --> 00:22:03,605
Give me Taehan Liquor.

368
00:22:03,605 --> 00:22:04,972
It was supposed to be Han Jun's anyway.

369
00:22:04,972 --> 00:22:06,005
What if I say no?

370
00:22:06,005 --> 00:22:10,272
You'll see for yourself why you
have no choice but to say yes.

371
00:22:10,272 --> 00:22:14,438
Well, it probably wasn't
that important a matter.

372
00:22:14,438 --> 00:22:16,105
Then I'll tell you again.

373
00:22:16,105 --> 00:22:19,405
Co-President of Taehan Liquor.

374
00:22:19,405 --> 00:22:21,405
Let's start from there.

375
00:22:21,405 --> 00:22:23,838
The murderer who killed
his brother for power.

376
00:22:23,838 --> 00:22:27,672
Du Jun has been through so much
because of this, you know.

377
00:22:27,672 --> 00:22:28,738
But what can I do?

378
00:22:28,738 --> 00:22:30,738
The next heir of Taehan Group

379
00:22:30,738 --> 00:22:35,472
abused drugs, even psychiatric medication.

380
00:22:36,738 --> 00:22:38,938
What should I do next?

381
00:22:38,938 --> 00:22:41,105
Knock it off!

382
00:22:42,338 --> 00:22:45,405
Once again, you only think of your son.

383
00:22:45,405 --> 00:22:49,272
The trauma from back then
can't repeat itself, right?

384
00:23:26,172 --> 00:23:27,438
What now, again?

385
00:23:27,438 --> 00:23:28,472
What brings you here?

386
00:23:28,472 --> 00:23:30,338
I guess you haven't heard yet.

387
00:23:30,338 --> 00:23:34,105
I'm here as the representative
of Taehan Liquor.

388
00:23:34,105 --> 00:23:35,838
What did you say?

389
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:47,272
As of today, we're co-presidents.

390
00:23:49,405 --> 00:23:50,505
Let's get along well.

391
00:23:50,505 --> 00:23:52,305
What does that mean?

392
00:23:52,305 --> 00:23:54,238
Co-presidents?

393
00:23:55,872 --> 00:23:58,972
The board discussed your dismissal.

394
00:23:58,972 --> 00:24:00,805
Who would entrust a company

395
00:24:00,805 --> 00:24:03,038
to someone relying on drugs to manage it?

396
00:24:03,038 --> 00:24:07,405
They claimed your press conference outburst
was due to unmedicated mood swings.

397
00:24:07,405 --> 00:24:11,105
That medication was properly
prescribed. Who would...

398
00:24:11,105 --> 00:24:13,672
Try saying that in front of the board.
Who would believe such a thing?

399
00:24:13,672 --> 00:24:17,238
I think the time for focusing
on the truth has passed.

400
00:24:17,238 --> 00:24:19,705
The board thinks that recently,

401
00:24:19,705 --> 00:24:21,138
your actions are not

402
00:24:21,138 --> 00:24:24,838
those of a company owner.

403
00:24:25,472 --> 00:24:29,472
So I'll be joining you for a while.

404
00:24:29,472 --> 00:24:32,638
I'll attend all meetings and schedules
going forward. Be aware.

405
00:24:32,638 --> 00:24:34,372
Then who decided this?

406
00:24:34,372 --> 00:24:36,638
- If the Chairman knew...
- It was the Chairman's decision.

407
00:24:36,638 --> 00:24:39,238
You hadn't heard yet?

408
00:24:39,238 --> 00:24:42,672
The communication between
father and son is really...

409
00:24:42,672 --> 00:24:44,405
Go ask him for the details.

410
00:24:44,405 --> 00:24:45,829
So,

411
00:24:45,829 --> 00:24:48,805
where should I sit?

412
00:24:57,838 --> 00:24:58,872
Unbelievable!

413
00:24:58,872 --> 00:25:01,038
Big news! Big news!

414
00:25:01,038 --> 00:25:04,472
We have a new co-president at our company!

415
00:25:04,472 --> 00:25:05,638
Then what about President Kang Du Jun?

416
00:25:05,638 --> 00:25:08,138
Rumor has it he's been
on psychiatric medication,

417
00:25:08,138 --> 00:25:09,438
quite a lot of it.

418
00:25:09,438 --> 00:25:10,872
The President? Is it fake news?

419
00:25:10,872 --> 00:25:16,372
No, because of the trauma, they say
daily life is impossible without medication.

420
00:25:16,372 --> 00:25:20,338
It hasn't even been long since the scandal
explanation, and now a drug controversy too.

421
00:25:20,338 --> 00:25:21,805
This might be quite troublesome.

422
00:25:21,805 --> 00:25:22,838
Right?

423
00:25:22,838 --> 00:25:25,172
So what will happen to President now?

424
00:25:25,172 --> 00:25:26,438
Is he getting kicked out?

425
00:25:26,438 --> 00:25:27,972
Huh?

426
00:25:27,972 --> 00:25:29,172
That's ridiculous.

427
00:25:29,172 --> 00:25:30,638
That can't be true.

428
00:25:30,638 --> 00:25:32,805
How would you know
whether it makes sense or not?

429
00:25:32,805 --> 00:25:36,438
Like last time, do you know
anything about this?

430
00:25:36,438 --> 00:25:39,172
- That's not it.
- It's not even verified information yet.

431
00:25:39,172 --> 00:25:40,305
Let's not jump to conclusions.

432
00:25:40,305 --> 00:25:42,638
The rumors could be distorted,
like with the previous scandal.

433
00:25:42,638 --> 00:25:45,838
Let's just trust him and wait.

434
00:25:45,838 --> 00:25:48,038
Yeah, our president would never.

435
00:25:48,038 --> 00:25:51,005
Oh, no way.

436
00:25:51,005 --> 00:25:54,005
Hey, tell them not to spread weird rumors.

437
00:25:54,005 --> 00:25:55,205
We have enough to worry about already.

438
00:25:55,205 --> 00:25:58,238
Anyway, this needs to be precise.

439
00:25:58,238 --> 00:26:00,672
After that day, whenever someone
touched my hand, even slightly,

440
00:26:00,672 --> 00:26:02,738
my body would freeze automatically.

441
00:26:02,738 --> 00:26:05,172
Is it because of his hands?

442
00:26:15,305 --> 00:26:16,485
[Market share trends by sales channel]

443
00:26:19,572 --> 00:26:22,192
[Risk flag for sales share trends by channel]
Convenience store channel share dropped

444
00:26:22,192 --> 00:26:24,338
from 23% last year to 19% this year.

445
00:26:24,338 --> 00:26:27,838
A four percent drop
is pretty serious, isn't it?

446
00:26:27,838 --> 00:26:31,372
Instead, big mart share rose by 3.8%.

447
00:26:31,372 --> 00:26:32,738
The margin here is much higher.

448
00:26:32,738 --> 00:26:36,872
For export volumes here,
the Southeast Asia margin rate is 12%.

449
00:26:36,872 --> 00:26:38,538
After shipping costs,
is there any profit left?

450
00:26:38,538 --> 00:26:42,772
You may not get it yet, but Southeast Asia
prioritizes market share capture.

451
00:26:42,772 --> 00:26:44,905
How long will you focus
solely on market share?

452
00:26:44,905 --> 00:26:47,138
Last month's
sales fulfillment rate was halved.

453
00:26:47,138 --> 00:26:49,172
When you ran the hotel, President Han,

454
00:26:49,172 --> 00:26:53,438
even if you lowered margins off-season,
wasn't room occupancy your priority?

455
00:26:53,438 --> 00:26:54,938
The liquor industry is no different.

456
00:26:54,938 --> 00:26:58,305
Shouldn't we consider
the entire industry is in a recession?

457
00:27:02,405 --> 00:27:04,138
Interesting.

458
00:27:05,105 --> 00:27:08,238
Speaking of which,
there's an ongoing in-house contest.

459
00:27:08,238 --> 00:27:09,305
How's that progressing?

460
00:27:09,305 --> 00:27:10,538
Ah, yes.

461
00:27:10,538 --> 00:27:11,605
Following Try Beer,

462
00:27:11,605 --> 00:27:14,038
we decided to actively incorporate
ideas from all employees

463
00:27:14,038 --> 00:27:16,472
to create the next flagship beer
for Taehan Liquor.

464
00:27:16,472 --> 00:27:18,272
And we're actually awarding cash prizes.

465
00:27:18,272 --> 00:27:20,101
[Finding the Next Try Beer]
We're even considering launching

466
00:27:20,101 --> 00:27:21,438
the first-place winner's idea as a product,

467
00:27:21,438 --> 00:27:23,845
so I hear the employees
are preparing diligently.

468
00:27:23,845 --> 00:27:26,272
[Award details]
Well, the prize money seems stingy for that.

469
00:27:26,272 --> 00:27:28,272
We should triple the prize money

470
00:27:28,272 --> 00:27:30,905
and most importantly, instead of
keeping this internal,

471
00:27:30,905 --> 00:27:32,772
we need to promote it widely,

472
00:27:32,772 --> 00:27:35,472
so consumers can get excited too.

473
00:27:35,472 --> 00:27:38,838
When the winning product launches,
let everyone try it themselves.

474
00:27:38,838 --> 00:27:40,572
What do you think?

475
00:27:46,638 --> 00:27:48,872
What's this? Domestic hop ale beer?

476
00:27:48,872 --> 00:27:51,772
[Domestic hop ale beer]
Yes, that's our team's new product.

477
00:27:51,772 --> 00:27:52,838
Domestic hops?

478
00:27:52,838 --> 00:27:53,938
Interesting.

479
00:27:53,938 --> 00:27:55,138
What's the production cost?

480
00:27:55,138 --> 00:27:58,438
- Well, the cost...
- It's still in testing phase.

481
00:27:59,472 --> 00:28:01,405
That makes cost control even more critical.

482
00:28:01,405 --> 00:28:05,105
Without cost management,
even the best idea is useless.

483
00:28:05,105 --> 00:28:06,805
Let's call the person in charge.

484
00:28:06,805 --> 00:28:09,005
- Pardon?
- Why do we need the person in charge here?

485
00:28:09,005 --> 00:28:11,472
If you're curious, ask me.

486
00:28:11,472 --> 00:28:12,472
Why?

487
00:28:12,472 --> 00:28:15,972
Is there a reason I can't call them directly?

488
00:28:28,772 --> 00:28:30,372
The concept is refreshing from the start.

489
00:28:30,372 --> 00:28:32,205
And it has market potential.

490
00:28:33,605 --> 00:28:34,638
Thank you.

491
00:28:34,638 --> 00:28:37,772
I'm curious about the proper way
to drink and appreciate it.

492
00:28:37,772 --> 00:28:39,605
Can you demonstrate it?

493
00:28:39,605 --> 00:28:43,138
From pouring into the glass to tasting.

494
00:28:43,972 --> 00:28:47,138
Why must it be done during the meeting?

495
00:28:47,138 --> 00:28:48,872
Ask me after the meeting is over.

496
00:28:48,872 --> 00:28:49,872
It'll be quick,

497
00:28:49,872 --> 00:28:52,138
and the person in charge is already here.

498
00:29:08,672 --> 00:29:10,338
I'm inexperienced in this,

499
00:29:10,338 --> 00:29:15,205
so I wanted to see how to pour
and taste it properly to enjoy the flavor.

500
00:29:15,205 --> 00:29:17,238
If she directly handled the product,

501
00:29:17,238 --> 00:29:19,538
it must be different, right?

502
00:29:33,338 --> 00:29:35,138
I apologize.

503
00:29:36,572 --> 00:29:37,572
Actually, I'm currently...

504
00:29:37,572 --> 00:29:39,405
Are you joking right now?

505
00:29:40,405 --> 00:29:42,949
Manager Jang, didn't you know the prototype
had quality issues

506
00:29:42,949 --> 00:29:45,072
so we scrapped the entire batch?

507
00:29:45,872 --> 00:29:48,905
I'm sorry, but I received a late report
that the hop farm had financial issues,

508
00:29:48,905 --> 00:29:51,605
which affected the prototype quality.

509
00:29:51,605 --> 00:29:55,338
I'll report to you as soon as
the redeveloped prototype is ready.

510
00:29:55,338 --> 00:29:57,805
It's my fault. I sincerely apologize.

511
00:29:57,805 --> 00:29:59,505
I'm sorry.

512
00:30:14,038 --> 00:30:16,805
So you are really pregnant?

513
00:30:16,805 --> 00:30:20,105
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you earlier.

514
00:30:20,105 --> 00:30:23,805
But I did my utmost
not to affect the project.

515
00:30:23,805 --> 00:30:25,805
I never neglected my duties

516
00:30:25,805 --> 00:30:27,938
due to pregnancy, not even once.

517
00:30:28,938 --> 00:30:30,305
So?

518
00:30:30,305 --> 00:30:33,105
I'll step down if I must.

519
00:30:33,105 --> 00:30:36,138
I'll prepare the handover.

520
00:30:40,572 --> 00:30:42,638
You're the one in charge, aren't you?

521
00:30:43,738 --> 00:30:44,738
Pardon?

522
00:30:44,738 --> 00:30:47,238
So you have to take responsibility
until the very end.

523
00:30:47,238 --> 00:30:49,005
Keep going as far as you can.

524
00:30:49,005 --> 00:30:51,305
Whether it's tasting or condition issues,

525
00:30:51,305 --> 00:30:53,072
get help from the team.

526
00:30:53,072 --> 00:30:54,338
Just because you're pregnant
doesn't mean you can't work.

527
00:30:54,338 --> 00:30:56,005
Don't be stubborn,

528
00:30:56,005 --> 00:30:58,405
trying to do everything alone.

529
00:31:06,172 --> 00:31:07,438
Team Leader.

530
00:31:07,438 --> 00:31:09,705
Why did you help me earlier?

531
00:31:09,705 --> 00:31:12,472
You don't even like me, Team Leader.

532
00:31:12,472 --> 00:31:14,205
Do I not?

533
00:31:15,738 --> 00:31:18,038
Well, you're my junior at work.

534
00:31:18,038 --> 00:31:19,738
What?

535
00:31:19,738 --> 00:31:22,672
I'm the only one who can scold you.

536
00:31:24,005 --> 00:31:26,372
- Team Leader.
- Get out.

537
00:31:39,405 --> 00:31:43,172
I explicitly told you not to mess with her.

538
00:31:45,872 --> 00:31:49,472
I've tolerated you this far out of respect
for my brother, but I have my limits.

539
00:31:49,472 --> 00:31:53,172
Do you think I came here just for you?

540
00:31:53,172 --> 00:31:55,005
What do you mean by that?

541
00:31:55,005 --> 00:31:57,405
Manager Jang is quite capable, you know.

542
00:31:57,405 --> 00:32:02,005
It's a shame that such talent
is overshadowed by you.

543
00:32:02,938 --> 00:32:05,438
Please just stay still.

544
00:32:05,438 --> 00:32:07,172
If you'd just stay put,

545
00:32:07,172 --> 00:32:10,405
I plan to give opportunities
to the capable Manager Jang to shine.

546
00:32:10,405 --> 00:32:12,838
But if you try to do something,

547
00:32:12,838 --> 00:32:15,738
I'll bet everything to block
Manager Jang's path.

548
00:32:15,738 --> 00:32:17,838
I'll do it if I decide to.

549
00:32:17,838 --> 00:32:19,005
You know that, right?

550
00:32:19,005 --> 00:32:20,205
Then give it your best shot.

551
00:32:20,205 --> 00:32:21,905
I'll also do whatever it takes this time

552
00:32:21,905 --> 00:32:25,105
to stop you, no matter what.

553
00:32:34,105 --> 00:32:35,805
Father!

554
00:32:35,805 --> 00:32:37,372
What on earth is going on?

555
00:32:37,372 --> 00:32:39,205
Did something happen with Jeong Eum?

556
00:32:39,205 --> 00:32:41,738
Looks like Moo Young and she
are really set on playing this game.

557
00:32:41,738 --> 00:32:44,005
They've swayed
the entire board to their side,

558
00:32:44,005 --> 00:32:46,605
so there was nothing I could do immediately.

559
00:32:46,605 --> 00:32:49,905
We don't need executives who only
care about their own interests.

560
00:32:49,905 --> 00:32:50,938
We should just take them all down at once.

561
00:32:50,938 --> 00:32:54,138
You know better than anyone
that's not the point.

562
00:32:54,138 --> 00:32:55,738
To overcome this situation,

563
00:32:55,738 --> 00:32:58,338
you must conquer it yourself.

564
00:32:58,338 --> 00:33:00,038
Otherwise that trauma

565
00:33:00,038 --> 00:33:03,905
will trip you up at another critical moment.

566
00:33:03,905 --> 00:33:06,238
Now it's your turn to show them.

567
00:33:06,238 --> 00:33:09,305
That this won't break you,

568
00:33:09,305 --> 00:33:12,205
that you can stand strong
without the medication.

569
00:33:12,205 --> 00:33:15,972
Focus on proving it yourself.

570
00:33:16,672 --> 00:33:19,872
I'll look into the board issue myself.

571
00:33:20,638 --> 00:33:22,338
Understood?

572
00:33:22,338 --> 00:33:24,038
Yes.

573
00:33:37,405 --> 00:33:39,772
Now it's your turn to show them.

574
00:33:39,772 --> 00:33:42,338
That this won't break you,

575
00:33:42,338 --> 00:33:44,305
that you can stand strong
without the medication.

576
00:33:44,305 --> 00:33:47,238
Focus on proving it yourself.

577
00:33:54,172 --> 00:33:56,072
President.

578
00:33:59,038 --> 00:34:00,705
What's on your mind?

579
00:34:00,705 --> 00:34:03,438
Nothing. You were really
startled earlier, weren't you?

580
00:34:03,438 --> 00:34:04,705
I should have stopped it beforehand.

581
00:34:04,705 --> 00:34:07,172
Is this the time to worry about me?

582
00:34:08,672 --> 00:34:12,572
I know exactly what kind of person she is.

583
00:34:12,572 --> 00:34:13,972
Will you really be okay?

584
00:34:13,972 --> 00:34:15,805
Co-presidents? Seriously?

585
00:34:15,805 --> 00:34:18,505
I'm already preparing countermeasures.

586
00:34:18,505 --> 00:34:22,138
I won't just sit back and take it this time,
so don't worry too much.

587
00:34:22,138 --> 00:34:23,138
I'll help too.

588
00:34:23,138 --> 00:34:24,272
Just tell me what to do.

589
00:34:24,272 --> 00:34:25,638
Leave this to me.

590
00:34:25,638 --> 00:34:28,338
Hui Won, just stay by my side as you are now.

591
00:34:28,338 --> 00:34:30,572
That's enough for me.

592
00:34:38,505 --> 00:34:39,805
The subscriber you are calling
is not available.

593
00:34:39,805 --> 00:34:42,072
- Mom, seriously.
- Please leave a message...

594
00:34:42,072 --> 00:34:43,269
[Mom]

595
00:34:50,438 --> 00:34:52,072
The subscriber you are calling
is not available.

596
00:34:52,072 --> 00:34:55,138
Oh my. What's going on?

597
00:35:17,372 --> 00:35:19,672
What were you even thinking?

598
00:35:21,705 --> 00:35:22,738
Mom.

599
00:35:22,738 --> 00:35:24,305
It's the board's decision.

600
00:35:24,305 --> 00:35:25,738
Is there any reason to refuse?

601
00:35:25,738 --> 00:35:26,738
That makes no sense.

602
00:35:26,738 --> 00:35:28,538
Uncle isn't taking weird drugs or anything.

603
00:35:28,538 --> 00:35:30,405
Why is the company pushing him like this?

604
00:35:30,405 --> 00:35:32,238
Are you really going as far as
proposing his dismissal?

605
00:35:32,238 --> 00:35:34,172
It was your dad's anyway.

606
00:35:34,172 --> 00:35:38,705
He would've passed Taehan Liquor to you.

607
00:35:38,705 --> 00:35:40,472
So it was you, Mom.

608
00:35:41,405 --> 00:35:42,772
You were behind it all.

609
00:35:42,772 --> 00:35:45,272
If you feel wronged,
participate in the voting.

610
00:35:45,272 --> 00:35:46,938
If you want to use your voting rights.

611
00:35:46,938 --> 00:35:48,905
How could you? You know
about my relationship with Uncle.

612
00:35:48,905 --> 00:35:51,772
Your uncle is the one
who made you lose your father.

613
00:35:51,772 --> 00:35:55,438
He's the one who destroyed our family.

614
00:35:55,438 --> 00:35:59,072
You think he'll still look out for you
once he has his own real family?

615
00:35:59,072 --> 00:36:00,072
Make your choice.

616
00:36:00,072 --> 00:36:01,705
Me or your uncle?

617
00:36:01,705 --> 00:36:02,872
That's ridiculous.

618
00:36:02,872 --> 00:36:05,905
What do I even have left?

619
00:36:05,905 --> 00:36:07,672
For me,

620
00:36:09,372 --> 00:36:11,605
you're all I've got now.

621
00:36:29,238 --> 00:36:30,572
In other words,

622
00:36:30,572 --> 00:36:33,905
since the drug scandal involving
President Kang Du Jun has erupted,

623
00:36:33,905 --> 00:36:37,505
our board has concluded
saving the situation is no longer possible.

624
00:36:37,505 --> 00:36:38,772
I can't accept this.

625
00:36:38,772 --> 00:36:40,705
Using someone's private
medical records like this?

626
00:36:40,705 --> 00:36:43,305
The President's health
isn't a private matter.

627
00:36:43,305 --> 00:36:45,305
It directly impacts the company's management.

628
00:36:45,305 --> 00:36:49,205
I even doubt whether the decisions
made so far were based on sound judgment.

629
00:36:49,205 --> 00:36:52,772
I've performed my duties with a sound mind,
and my track record proves it.

630
00:36:52,772 --> 00:36:55,572
Would someone like that
commit such impulsive acts?

631
00:36:55,572 --> 00:36:59,672
You can't even manage a simple
handshake at official events.

632
00:36:59,672 --> 00:37:04,172
Isn't the fact that you haven't
overcome that handshake trauma

633
00:37:04,172 --> 00:37:06,672
already a sign of insufficient
leadership qualities?

634
00:37:06,672 --> 00:37:08,605
For a businessperson,
a handshake signifies trust.

635
00:37:08,605 --> 00:37:11,972
Is it acceptable to fail
to build even that much trust?

636
00:37:11,972 --> 00:37:13,989
That's true.

637
00:37:13,989 --> 00:37:17,138
Makes sense, he can't even do that.

638
00:37:17,138 --> 00:37:21,305
Why not step down voluntarily at this point?

639
00:37:21,305 --> 00:37:25,905
Rumors are widespread that you hold
the position by bloodline, not merit.

640
00:37:25,905 --> 00:37:28,772
At least do it
if there's any conscience left.

641
00:37:28,772 --> 00:37:30,438
Let's just start voting right now.

642
00:37:30,438 --> 00:37:32,672
Exactly. What's the point of delaying?

643
00:37:32,672 --> 00:37:34,172
The result will be the same anyway.

644
00:37:34,172 --> 00:37:38,341
- Fine.
- Let's vote right now.

645
00:37:38,341 --> 00:37:40,505
- Let's vote.
- Come on.

646
00:37:40,505 --> 00:37:43,372
Well, if that's how everyone feels,

647
00:37:43,372 --> 00:37:44,672
we'll proceed with the vote now...

648
00:37:44,672 --> 00:37:48,905
Board matters must be notified
at least a week in advance.

649
00:37:48,905 --> 00:37:51,938
I surely mentioned it
on the day I came to work.

650
00:37:51,938 --> 00:37:54,538
That your dismissal would soon
be discussed at the board meeting.

651
00:37:54,538 --> 00:37:57,638
Is a casual remark in the office
considered legal notice?

652
00:37:58,372 --> 00:38:00,838
Decisions made by a board meeting
with stakeholders directly involved

653
00:38:00,838 --> 00:38:02,772
may have legal issues.

654
00:38:02,772 --> 00:38:04,638
If you insist on voting today,

655
00:38:04,638 --> 00:38:08,172
I will hold every single person
here accountable.

656
00:38:08,172 --> 00:38:09,637
Do you

657
00:38:09,637 --> 00:38:11,838
still wish to proceed?

658
00:38:16,705 --> 00:38:19,772
So what exactly are you trying to say?

659
00:38:19,772 --> 00:38:21,738
Give me two weeks.

660
00:38:21,738 --> 00:38:25,538
I'm asking for the chance to explain myself
through proper procedures.

661
00:38:25,538 --> 00:38:27,493
It's not too late

662
00:38:27,493 --> 00:38:29,938
to vote then.

663
00:38:41,938 --> 00:38:45,738
Does he really think he can get
anything done in two weeks?

664
00:38:45,738 --> 00:38:47,072
Not a chance.

665
00:38:47,072 --> 00:38:50,172
What's in it for you joining forces with her?

666
00:38:51,738 --> 00:38:53,072
What's this all of a sudden?

667
00:38:53,072 --> 00:38:57,672
Do you really think she will
stand with you until the end?

668
00:38:57,672 --> 00:38:59,572
Don't even think about provoking me.

669
00:38:59,572 --> 00:39:01,072
It's a waste of time anyway.

670
00:39:01,072 --> 00:39:04,472
The incident fifteen years ago,
you remember it, right?

671
00:39:06,538 --> 00:39:09,838
Those of you who helped turn me
into a murderer back then.

672
00:39:09,838 --> 00:39:15,372
The journalists you were close with then
are now all department heads or deputy heads.

673
00:39:15,372 --> 00:39:18,772
It's all in the past.
What can you possibly do?

674
00:39:18,772 --> 00:39:22,605
True. Unfortunately, there's no
evidence for that case.

675
00:39:22,605 --> 00:39:24,505
Then how about this?

676
00:39:24,505 --> 00:39:28,772
You've been manipulating the financial
statements little by little for 11 years.

677
00:39:28,772 --> 00:39:33,338
Do you really think I don't know
where all that slush fund money went?

678
00:39:35,838 --> 00:39:38,305
Fortunately, I haven't told Father yet.

679
00:39:38,305 --> 00:39:40,305
But he'll find out soon enough.

680
00:39:40,305 --> 00:39:42,072
Wait a minute.

681
00:39:42,072 --> 00:39:44,305
Let me think for a moment...

682
00:39:44,305 --> 00:39:46,538
I'm giving you an opportunity right now.

683
00:39:46,538 --> 00:39:49,138
Cut ties with her and persuade the board.

684
00:39:49,138 --> 00:39:51,905
If it goes to prosecution,
you are finished too.

685
00:39:51,905 --> 00:39:53,938
You understand that, right?

686
00:39:58,638 --> 00:40:00,338
No, wait...

687
00:40:08,038 --> 00:40:10,172
So, how was it?

688
00:40:10,172 --> 00:40:11,938
Did it hit the mark?

689
00:40:11,938 --> 00:40:13,405
Seems like he roughly understood.

690
00:40:13,405 --> 00:40:15,005
So what are you going to do now?

691
00:40:15,005 --> 00:40:16,972
I'm going to stick with the plan.

692
00:40:16,972 --> 00:40:19,672
I've thrown out the bait,
so something will bite.

693
00:40:19,672 --> 00:40:21,372
When are you going to reveal the evidence?

694
00:40:21,372 --> 00:40:22,672
When the time is right.

695
00:40:22,672 --> 00:40:24,338
Not yet. I need to save it.

696
00:40:24,338 --> 00:40:26,905
Whew, my heart's pounding.

697
00:40:26,905 --> 00:40:31,138
By the way, shouldn't you tell
Ms. Hui Won about today's board meeting?

698
00:40:32,172 --> 00:40:34,238
She needs to know your situation right now.

699
00:40:34,238 --> 00:40:35,772
Keep it a secret from Hui Won.

700
00:40:35,772 --> 00:40:37,005
Why?

701
00:40:37,005 --> 00:40:39,438
She's with child.
I'm sure it's tough for her.

702
00:40:39,438 --> 00:40:41,738
I want to stop making her worry.

703
00:40:42,572 --> 00:40:44,272
But...

704
00:40:48,672 --> 00:40:49,705
Tak Soo.

705
00:40:49,705 --> 00:40:51,338
[Packaging, Campaign Slogan]
I asked for those images earlier.

706
00:40:51,338 --> 00:40:52,405
[Market Analysis]
Give me those images.

707
00:40:52,405 --> 00:40:53,538
Ah, it's right here.

708
00:40:53,538 --> 00:40:54,638
Send those over quickly.

709
00:40:54,638 --> 00:40:55,638
[Target &amp; Branding Strategy]
Sent.

710
00:40:55,638 --> 00:40:57,372
Assistant Manager Choi, please just go home.

711
00:40:57,372 --> 00:40:58,472
[Revenue Projections, Distribution Strategy]
Jeez.

712
00:40:58,472 --> 00:41:00,272
Check the bottom part.

713
00:41:00,272 --> 00:41:02,272
The prize money tripling is great news,

714
00:41:02,272 --> 00:41:05,205
but isn't it unfair that
we can't submit as a team?

715
00:41:05,205 --> 00:41:08,305
Still, it's such a relief that
everyone's developing their own stuff.

716
00:41:08,305 --> 00:41:09,438
I'm almost done.

717
00:41:09,438 --> 00:41:10,605
Let me know if you need help.

718
00:41:10,605 --> 00:41:11,872
Manager Jang, help me out.

719
00:41:11,872 --> 00:41:14,438
Look at this. Fix this part.

720
00:41:14,438 --> 00:41:16,572
[Upload Complete]
Even if I fix this, it still doesn't work.

721
00:41:16,572 --> 00:41:18,438
Assistant Manager Choi, please go home.

722
00:41:18,438 --> 00:41:20,272
- Se Hyeon, do you need anything?
- I'm just so worried.

723
00:41:20,272 --> 00:41:21,305
Tak Soo, I told you to send me that earlier.

724
00:41:21,305 --> 00:41:24,138
It's okay. You always look out
for me and help me.

725
00:41:24,138 --> 00:41:25,305
- I'll handle it myself.
- That's why I asked.

726
00:41:25,305 --> 00:41:26,872
- Oh, yeah?
- It's not my fault, okay?

727
00:41:26,872 --> 00:41:29,438
- But if you need anything, just say it.
- You just go home!

728
00:41:29,438 --> 00:41:31,638
Yes, thank you.

729
00:41:33,538 --> 00:41:34,838
Why? What's wrong?

730
00:41:34,838 --> 00:41:35,972
Huh? What's happening?

731
00:41:35,972 --> 00:41:37,338
Why did it suddenly stop?

732
00:41:37,338 --> 00:41:39,172
Jeez, get a grip.

733
00:41:39,172 --> 00:41:42,238
Seeing this, I think we're
the real winners for giving up early.

734
00:41:42,238 --> 00:41:44,772
Right? But seeing them prepare
for the contest while so busy,

735
00:41:44,772 --> 00:41:45,805
they're all amazing.

736
00:41:45,805 --> 00:41:47,538
I admit that.

737
00:41:48,472 --> 00:41:51,472
What's wrong? What!

738
00:41:51,472 --> 00:41:54,038
Yes! It's working again!

739
00:41:55,365 --> 00:41:57,305
Jeez.

740
00:41:57,305 --> 00:41:59,138
[Target &amp; Branding Strategy]
No typos...

741
00:41:59,138 --> 00:42:00,505
Save.

742
00:42:00,505 --> 00:42:02,505
[Upload Complete]
All done.

743
00:42:02,505 --> 00:42:04,072
- Submission complete.
- I'm exhausted.

744
00:42:04,072 --> 00:42:05,238
I feel like I did all of this.

745
00:42:05,238 --> 00:42:06,405
[Upload Complete]
Look at me sweating.

746
00:42:06,405 --> 00:42:08,405
I'm done too.

747
00:42:09,038 --> 00:42:10,805
Alright then.

748
00:42:10,805 --> 00:42:12,138
The contest is over now.

749
00:42:12,138 --> 00:42:14,472
- Let's have pork belly after work!
- I'm in!

750
00:42:14,472 --> 00:42:16,705
I have to bathe the kids today.

751
00:42:16,705 --> 00:42:19,338
Then Manager Nah will pass.
What about the rest?

752
00:42:19,338 --> 00:42:21,338
Assistant Manager Choi!
Skipping me just like that?

753
00:42:21,338 --> 00:42:23,372
I'll go. Everyone else
is okay with it, right?

754
00:42:23,372 --> 00:42:25,605
Ah, I have plans today.

755
00:42:25,605 --> 00:42:27,072
- I'm sorry.
- Come on.

756
00:42:27,072 --> 00:42:28,472
Ah, why?

757
00:42:28,472 --> 00:42:31,305
I've been pushing myself too hard
lately, so I'm not feeling well.

758
00:42:31,305 --> 00:42:32,305
Ah, really?

759
00:42:32,305 --> 00:42:36,338
When your condition is off,
one shot of soju will wipe the fatigue.

760
00:42:36,338 --> 00:42:38,672
Why are you pressuring
someone who's unwell to drink?

761
00:42:38,672 --> 00:42:40,472
I didn't force it, but I'm just disappointed.

762
00:42:40,472 --> 00:42:43,205
I know, she must be the most disappointed.

763
00:42:43,205 --> 00:42:45,272
Why are you feeling
disappointed on her behalf?

764
00:42:45,272 --> 00:42:49,838
If anyone in our team forces alcohol,
you'll get a serious scolding from me.

765
00:42:49,838 --> 00:42:50,838
Got it?

766
00:42:50,838 --> 00:42:52,638
Yes.

767
00:42:52,638 --> 00:42:54,272
What's gotten into Team Leader?

768
00:42:54,272 --> 00:42:56,938
Taking Manager Jang's side completely?

769
00:42:56,938 --> 00:42:57,972
Exactly.

770
00:42:57,972 --> 00:42:59,405
When did I ever force anyone?

771
00:42:59,405 --> 00:43:01,972
The leader does the forcing daily!

772
00:43:01,972 --> 00:43:03,705
I can hear everything.

773
00:43:04,638 --> 00:43:05,638
What should we eat?

774
00:43:05,638 --> 00:43:06,705
Let's have pork belly.

775
00:43:06,705 --> 00:43:07,705
I know a place.

776
00:43:07,705 --> 00:43:10,572
There's a great spot nearby.
It's newly opened, and it's amazing.

777
00:43:10,572 --> 00:43:12,305
Nice.

778
00:43:21,405 --> 00:43:23,572
Doors closing.

779
00:43:25,172 --> 00:43:27,838
By the way, I apologize for last time.

780
00:43:27,838 --> 00:43:30,472
I momentarily forgot you were pregnant.

781
00:43:30,472 --> 00:43:31,472
It's okay.

782
00:43:31,472 --> 00:43:33,138
You're not happy I came, are you?

783
00:43:33,138 --> 00:43:37,305
You wonder if I'm scheming again
around him, right?

784
00:43:38,805 --> 00:43:41,605
I can't say I don't.

785
00:43:41,605 --> 00:43:45,072
I'm not someone who mixes
personal feelings into work.

786
00:43:45,072 --> 00:43:48,938
When I look at you,
it's like seeing my old self.

787
00:43:48,938 --> 00:43:51,372
That's why I feel more invested, perhaps.

788
00:43:51,372 --> 00:43:55,138
Especially after reviewing
the projects you handled recently.

789
00:43:55,138 --> 00:43:57,738
Honestly, I see you in a new light.

790
00:43:59,338 --> 00:44:02,838
I want to properly support you going forward.

791
00:44:02,838 --> 00:44:05,305
- What do you mean?
- Just tell me what you want.

792
00:44:05,305 --> 00:44:07,872
I can support you with anything.

793
00:44:07,872 --> 00:44:10,138
Your dream.

794
00:44:11,038 --> 00:44:13,338
I can make it come true.

795
00:44:13,338 --> 00:44:16,272
No, you don't need to do that.

796
00:44:17,172 --> 00:44:19,705
I've done well

797
00:44:20,838 --> 00:44:23,338
on my own so far.

798
00:44:23,338 --> 00:44:25,338
And my dream

799
00:44:26,438 --> 00:44:30,705
wouldn't mean anything
if someone forced it to happen.

800
00:44:32,517 --> 00:44:33,541
Doors opening.

801
00:44:33,541 --> 00:44:37,238
Thank you for the offer, though.

802
00:44:37,238 --> 00:44:38,972
Then...

803
00:44:44,305 --> 00:44:47,238
Is it true our company president
went to yours?

804
00:44:47,238 --> 00:44:50,038
But didn't you say she is
your president's sister-in-law?

805
00:44:50,038 --> 00:44:52,972
What is this? It's not even
a sibling rivalry. Is it a family feud?

806
00:44:52,972 --> 00:44:54,705
It just made the company atmosphere awkward.

807
00:44:54,705 --> 00:44:56,838
Ugh, this is making me dizzy.

808
00:44:56,838 --> 00:44:57,925
So where are you now?

809
00:44:57,925 --> 00:44:59,405
Me? On my way home.

810
00:44:59,405 --> 00:45:00,472
Huh? Let's get food.

811
00:45:00,472 --> 00:45:01,572
I'm heading home now too.

812
00:45:01,572 --> 00:45:03,905
Now? I want to rest a bit today.

813
00:45:03,905 --> 00:45:04,938
Huh?

814
00:45:04,938 --> 00:45:06,838
Min Uk is probably waiting by now.

815
00:45:06,838 --> 00:45:08,538
Huh?

816
00:45:26,905 --> 00:45:28,638
- Well...
- Well...

817
00:45:29,272 --> 00:45:31,105
- You go first.
- No.

818
00:45:31,105 --> 00:45:32,805
You go first.

819
00:45:32,805 --> 00:45:35,105
Mine's not a big deal.

820
00:45:36,772 --> 00:45:39,872
How's the President doing lately?

821
00:45:39,872 --> 00:45:42,905
Strange rumors are going around the company.

822
00:45:44,205 --> 00:45:49,538
I heard before he was suffering
from something like insomnia.

823
00:45:49,538 --> 00:45:51,372
It seems he's still

824
00:45:51,372 --> 00:45:53,605
being misunderstood because of it.

825
00:45:53,605 --> 00:45:55,472
But I'm not sure.

826
00:45:55,472 --> 00:45:59,172
He doesn't tell me the details.

827
00:45:59,872 --> 00:46:02,472
I guess he's worried you might worry.

828
00:46:05,572 --> 00:46:09,205
I can guess what's troubling him,

829
00:46:09,205 --> 00:46:12,305
but I can't solve it for him right now.

830
00:46:13,138 --> 00:46:16,805
That makes me feel a bit sorry and sad.

831
00:46:22,505 --> 00:46:25,738
Yeah, this is exactly Jang Hui Won.

832
00:46:25,738 --> 00:46:30,205
You stand up for others' problems
like they're your own.

833
00:46:35,638 --> 00:46:38,672
That's always been your admirable quality.

834
00:46:38,672 --> 00:46:43,172
But I think I was too focused on myself.

835
00:46:43,172 --> 00:46:44,305
Sorry.

836
00:46:44,305 --> 00:46:46,705
- Hey.
- So don't worry about it.

837
00:46:46,705 --> 00:46:51,305
With our bond this strong,
no storm can shake us, right?

838
00:46:51,972 --> 00:46:53,701
Still,

839
00:46:53,701 --> 00:46:54,872
tell me if you need help.

840
00:46:54,872 --> 00:46:57,272
I'll always be on your side.

841
00:46:58,572 --> 00:47:00,305
Okay.

842
00:47:01,205 --> 00:47:03,872
Let's go. Mi Ran must be waiting.

843
00:47:03,872 --> 00:47:05,572
Yeah.

844
00:47:08,472 --> 00:47:11,372
Are you available for a quick call?

845
00:47:14,272 --> 00:47:15,305
The dismissal proposal?

846
00:47:15,305 --> 00:47:17,938
Yes, Du Jun told me not to tell you.

847
00:47:17,938 --> 00:47:21,338
But I felt you needed to know, Ms. Hui Won.

848
00:47:21,338 --> 00:47:22,372
Ah.

849
00:47:22,372 --> 00:47:25,072
Since you're the most important
person to Du Jun right now.

850
00:47:25,072 --> 00:47:26,872
If you're by his side,

851
00:47:26,872 --> 00:47:32,438
he might feel comfortable
enough to unburden himself.

852
00:47:48,272 --> 00:47:49,338
What happened?

853
00:47:49,338 --> 00:47:51,472
What's going on with the President?

854
00:47:51,472 --> 00:47:53,838
There seems to be internal complications.

855
00:47:53,838 --> 00:47:56,638
I want to help the President,

856
00:47:56,638 --> 00:47:57,672
but I don't know how.

857
00:47:57,672 --> 00:47:58,772
I heard at the company

858
00:47:58,772 --> 00:48:01,338
that the President can't shake hands.

859
00:48:01,338 --> 00:48:02,605
Could it be because of that?

860
00:48:02,605 --> 00:48:03,605
Shake hands?

861
00:48:03,605 --> 00:48:06,213
Oh, a psychological issue?

862
00:48:06,949 --> 00:48:10,438
How about therapy together?

863
00:48:10,438 --> 00:48:13,805
He already goes to therapy, I believe.

864
00:48:13,805 --> 00:48:15,938
But I don't mean anything fancy.

865
00:48:15,938 --> 00:48:18,538
Just having a drink with you guys,
talking over my worries,

866
00:48:18,538 --> 00:48:20,172
and maybe trashing some people a bit

867
00:48:20,172 --> 00:48:21,772
can make me feel so much better.

868
00:48:21,772 --> 00:48:22,772
Hey, who knows?

869
00:48:22,772 --> 00:48:26,938
If he just spills his thoughts
over a drink with you...

870
00:48:26,938 --> 00:48:28,972
Oh, right, you can't drink.

871
00:48:28,972 --> 00:48:30,972
What a shame.

872
00:48:32,372 --> 00:48:34,638
Spill his thoughts?

873
00:48:36,338 --> 00:48:39,305
I think I should go see him.

874
00:48:39,305 --> 00:48:40,338
Huh? What?

875
00:48:40,338 --> 00:48:41,772
What about dessert?

876
00:48:41,772 --> 00:48:43,538
Sorry, today you guys go without me.

877
00:48:43,538 --> 00:48:44,838
I'll contact you later.

878
00:48:44,838 --> 00:48:46,105
Uh, well...

879
00:48:46,105 --> 00:48:50,072
Then we'll just have dessert ourselves.

880
00:48:54,738 --> 00:48:56,872
Let's just eat this and go.

881
00:48:56,872 --> 00:48:57,905
Huh?

882
00:48:57,905 --> 00:48:59,872
Didn't you say we were
going for dessert earlier?

883
00:48:59,872 --> 00:49:00,938
No.

884
00:49:00,938 --> 00:49:03,472
I'll just head home early to rest.

885
00:49:09,472 --> 00:49:12,972
About himself, therapy?

886
00:49:17,605 --> 00:49:20,572
[Trauma Treatment]

887
00:49:20,572 --> 00:49:22,272
[Group Counseling]

888
00:49:22,272 --> 00:49:25,925
[Group Therapy]

889
00:49:27,005 --> 00:49:29,638
Do I even have the right to do this?

890
00:49:31,238 --> 00:49:34,405
I haven't solved my own issues yet.

891
00:49:55,472 --> 00:49:57,138
President.

892
00:49:57,138 --> 00:49:59,472
What brings you here, Hui Won?

893
00:50:01,238 --> 00:50:03,972
What a liar.

894
00:50:03,972 --> 00:50:05,738
- What?
- You didn't mention the dismissal proposal.

895
00:50:05,738 --> 00:50:07,372
Didn't tell me what's troubling you.

896
00:50:07,372 --> 00:50:10,538
And never once asked for my help.

897
00:50:10,538 --> 00:50:12,105
After giving me all that lecture,

898
00:50:12,105 --> 00:50:13,572
you keep doing this yourself?

899
00:50:13,572 --> 00:50:14,572
I feel hurt.

900
00:50:14,572 --> 00:50:17,305
But how did you...

901
00:50:17,305 --> 00:50:20,938
- That Secretary Go.
- Don't you dare blame Secretary Go.

902
00:50:23,005 --> 00:50:24,472
It's just

903
00:50:24,472 --> 00:50:28,538
this is my problem to solve.

904
00:50:30,438 --> 00:50:32,605
You seem to think things

905
00:50:32,605 --> 00:50:36,738
only have meaning if solved immediately.

906
00:50:36,738 --> 00:50:38,972
But sometimes,

907
00:50:38,972 --> 00:50:44,172
just sharing worries has meaning too.

908
00:50:44,172 --> 00:50:46,605
When I developed the new product,

909
00:50:46,605 --> 00:50:51,005
I tried crafting recipes
and hop blends alone,

910
00:50:51,005 --> 00:50:55,972
but my first attempts were always disasters.

911
00:50:55,972 --> 00:51:00,005
Then when we taste-tested
with the team and talked it out,

912
00:51:00,005 --> 00:51:03,505
I started seeing solutions.

913
00:51:03,505 --> 00:51:07,005
Not that we found any grand solution,

914
00:51:07,005 --> 00:51:08,772
but

915
00:51:08,772 --> 00:51:13,272
sharing made the path clearer.

916
00:51:22,338 --> 00:51:24,438
So I want to ask,

917
00:51:24,438 --> 00:51:27,738
are you free the day after tomorrow?

918
00:51:27,738 --> 00:51:30,605
I need you, President.

919
00:51:41,905 --> 00:51:43,905
Would this be okay?

920
00:51:45,338 --> 00:51:50,005
Since you talked about Mom last time,
I couldn't call her first.

921
00:51:50,005 --> 00:51:51,938
Just thinking about her,

922
00:51:51,938 --> 00:51:56,105
I feel lost on where to begin.

923
00:51:56,972 --> 00:51:59,638
But if you're with me,

924
00:51:59,638 --> 00:52:03,138
I think I'll find courage.

925
00:52:03,138 --> 00:52:04,138
Well done.

926
00:52:04,138 --> 00:52:06,438
Don't worry, I'll stick right by you.

927
00:52:06,438 --> 00:52:08,138
Let's go.

928
00:52:15,238 --> 00:52:19,738
It's been four years
since my daughter has been a shut-in.

929
00:52:19,738 --> 00:52:22,005
I was even kneeling at the door.

930
00:52:22,005 --> 00:52:25,072
- I've hated my father my whole life.
- But she wouldn't come out.

931
00:52:25,072 --> 00:52:26,505
- Because he hit me a lot.
- Let alone see me.

932
00:52:26,505 --> 00:52:28,505
- When I was a sophomore in college...
- When I look at her...

933
00:52:28,505 --> 00:52:30,138
It's all my fault.

934
00:52:30,138 --> 00:52:31,138
If only he had said that one thing...

935
00:52:31,138 --> 00:52:33,638
I want to see Ju Won's face.

936
00:52:33,638 --> 00:52:35,838
- I wouldn't have to resent him like this.
- I want to hold her hand just once.

937
00:52:35,838 --> 00:52:37,872
Let's give him some time.

938
00:52:37,872 --> 00:52:41,372
Is there anyone else?

939
00:52:54,805 --> 00:52:58,105
Yes, would you like to share?

940
00:53:00,172 --> 00:53:02,038
I...

941
00:53:07,838 --> 00:53:12,838
I have a difficult relationship with my mom.

942
00:53:13,605 --> 00:53:15,405
My mom always

943
00:53:15,405 --> 00:53:20,238
thought I ruined her life.

944
00:53:20,938 --> 00:53:22,538
So she constantly said

945
00:53:22,538 --> 00:53:24,933
that it's

946
00:53:24,933 --> 00:53:27,305
all my fault.

947
00:53:27,305 --> 00:53:30,638
My life got completely ruined because of you.

948
00:53:30,638 --> 00:53:33,238
If it weren't for you, I...

949
00:53:33,238 --> 00:53:34,905
If it weren't for you...

950
00:53:34,905 --> 00:53:37,138
Giving birth to you was
a mistake from the start.

951
00:53:37,138 --> 00:53:39,905
My life has been a mess
ever since then. Satisfied?

952
00:53:39,905 --> 00:53:41,105
You bad girl.

953
00:53:41,105 --> 00:53:43,372
How can you only think
about yourself until the very end?

954
00:53:43,372 --> 00:53:46,872
You should never have been born.

955
00:53:46,872 --> 00:53:48,605
But now,

956
00:53:50,272 --> 00:53:53,872
I'm about to become a mom.

957
00:53:53,872 --> 00:53:55,272
Oh my, congratulations!

958
00:53:55,272 --> 00:53:57,505
Everyone, let's give her a round of applause.

959
00:53:57,505 --> 00:54:00,138
Congratulations, really.

960
00:54:07,805 --> 00:54:11,005
I always

961
00:54:11,005 --> 00:54:15,738
gave up and avoided dealing with my mom.

962
00:54:15,738 --> 00:54:18,905
So when I realized I'm becoming a mom,

963
00:54:18,905 --> 00:54:21,438
I was really scared at first.

964
00:54:21,438 --> 00:54:23,338
Afraid I might say

965
00:54:23,338 --> 00:54:24,472
to my child,

966
00:54:24,472 --> 00:54:27,638
'it's all your fault,'

967
00:54:27,638 --> 00:54:30,338
like my mom did.

968
00:54:30,338 --> 00:54:34,972
But after meeting my baby's dad,

969
00:54:34,972 --> 00:54:40,505
who promised to care for
and protect me consistently,

970
00:54:40,505 --> 00:54:43,905
I felt this inexplicable confidence.

971
00:54:44,938 --> 00:54:47,405
Thanks to him,

972
00:54:47,405 --> 00:54:49,638
I want to understand

973
00:54:50,305 --> 00:54:52,838
my mom better.

974
00:54:58,672 --> 00:55:03,905
Because I want to give
this child proper love.

975
00:55:03,905 --> 00:55:07,105
To do that, I need to first...

976
00:55:09,238 --> 00:55:11,172
With my mom...

977
00:55:12,872 --> 00:55:13,905
My mom...

978
00:55:13,905 --> 00:55:18,138
You want to restore
your relationship with your mom, right?

979
00:55:18,138 --> 00:55:20,105
Yes.

980
00:55:20,105 --> 00:55:21,905
That's why I came here.

981
00:55:21,905 --> 00:55:23,438
You came to the right place, really.

982
00:55:23,438 --> 00:55:24,972
Let's give her a round of applause.

983
00:55:24,972 --> 00:55:27,005
Welcome.

984
00:55:54,738 --> 00:55:56,938
I'm so happy for you.

985
00:55:56,938 --> 00:55:59,405
- Thank you.
- See you next time.

986
00:56:03,772 --> 00:56:05,705
You did well.

987
00:56:06,872 --> 00:56:09,138
You did great, really.
It couldn't have been easy.

988
00:56:09,138 --> 00:56:10,905
I learned all this from you, President.

989
00:56:10,905 --> 00:56:13,138
- Huh?
- During your press conference that day,

990
00:56:13,138 --> 00:56:18,138
you calmly shared your story
in front of all those people, right?

991
00:56:18,138 --> 00:56:20,905
I don't think everything will be
resolved with this one attempt.

992
00:56:20,905 --> 00:56:24,805
I'm just trying to
think of it as the first step.

993
00:56:26,505 --> 00:56:27,705
Shall we go then?

994
00:56:27,705 --> 00:56:29,438
Yes.

995
00:56:38,138 --> 00:56:41,672
Don't let go. Don't give up, please!

996
00:56:41,672 --> 00:56:44,138
I don't think everything will be
resolved with this one attempt.

997
00:56:44,138 --> 00:56:47,538
I'm just trying to
think of it as the first step.

998
00:56:48,338 --> 00:56:50,038
You came to work early.

999
00:56:50,038 --> 00:56:54,572
I got one iced and one hot.
Which one do you want?

1000
00:57:01,738 --> 00:57:04,272
What are you doing? My arms are tired.

1001
00:57:30,538 --> 00:57:32,272
I'll enjoy it.

1002
00:57:35,472 --> 00:57:37,505
What's up with him?

1003
00:57:39,972 --> 00:57:42,405
But isn't Manager Nah's idea
really good this time?

1004
00:57:44,538 --> 00:57:46,838
This high-proof beer
can definitely win first place!

1005
00:57:46,838 --> 00:57:48,738
The three of us worked on it together!

1006
00:57:48,738 --> 00:57:50,772
My precious bunnies!

1007
00:57:52,038 --> 00:57:53,472
Just like him, right?

1008
00:57:53,472 --> 00:57:55,205
Oh, wait a minute!

1009
00:57:55,205 --> 00:57:56,405
Assistant Manager Choi,
Assistant Manager Choi!

1010
00:57:56,405 --> 00:57:57,905
- Hey, Kim Tak Soo!
- Kim Tak Soo!

1011
00:57:57,905 --> 00:58:00,338
Oh, I'm sorry.

1012
00:58:00,338 --> 00:58:04,005
Oh! The contest results are announced today!

1013
00:58:04,005 --> 00:58:05,972
- Focus.
- Really?

1014
00:58:05,972 --> 00:58:07,872
[Today's 2 PM awards ceremony]
So we're going to the awards ceremony?

1015
00:58:07,872 --> 00:58:09,205
Aren't they announcing
and then having the ceremony?

1016
00:58:09,205 --> 00:58:11,305
Right? Why did it change again?

1017
00:58:11,305 --> 00:58:13,605
Maybe they're planning
to give me first place today.

1018
00:58:13,605 --> 00:58:15,872
Oh.

1019
00:58:15,872 --> 00:58:17,205
Do you have eye drops?

1020
00:58:17,205 --> 00:58:18,438
Should I stick some in your eyes for you?

1021
00:58:18,438 --> 00:58:19,672
Never mind.

1022
00:58:19,672 --> 00:58:23,138
Ah, what should I do
when I get the prize money?

1023
00:58:23,138 --> 00:58:24,293
[Taehan Liquor 1st in-house
beer brand contest awards ceremony]

1024
00:58:24,293 --> 00:58:27,424
- Everyone stay seated.
- Who's won the first place?

1025
00:58:28,105 --> 00:58:29,905
Se Hyeon, heard anything?

1026
00:58:29,905 --> 00:58:31,272
No, I haven't either.

1027
00:58:31,272 --> 00:58:32,272
Huh?

1028
00:58:32,272 --> 00:58:33,305
Oh! Thank you.

1029
00:58:33,305 --> 00:58:36,738
I dedicate this award
to my beloved wife and my kids.

1030
00:58:36,738 --> 00:58:37,938
Oh, this doesn't seem right.

1031
00:58:37,938 --> 00:58:40,005
Someone might think
you actually won first place.

1032
00:58:40,005 --> 00:58:42,072
But didn't they say getting selected
means a guaranteed promotion?

1033
00:58:42,072 --> 00:58:45,172
Ah, I really should throw
a beef party for our little ones.

1034
00:58:45,172 --> 00:58:47,105
Even friends at other companies
keep asking about it lately.

1035
00:58:47,105 --> 00:58:49,638
If I knew it would grow this big,
I would have entered too.

1036
00:58:49,638 --> 00:58:51,138
So you should've done well earlier.

1037
00:58:51,138 --> 00:58:53,238
What's the point regretting now?

1038
00:58:55,105 --> 00:58:56,405
Manager, aren't you excited?

1039
00:58:56,405 --> 00:58:59,772
Right, you even stayed late
because of this and worked so hard.

1040
00:58:59,772 --> 00:59:01,538
Seems like I was really
desperate for it after so long.

1041
00:59:01,538 --> 00:59:05,305
But after giving it my all,
I feel more relieved than hopeful.

1042
00:59:05,305 --> 00:59:06,405
Me too.

1043
00:59:06,405 --> 00:59:08,972
It would be amazing if our team
got 1st, 2nd, and 3rd place, right?

1044
00:59:08,972 --> 00:59:10,205
- I'm getting first, right?
- Huh?

1045
00:59:10,205 --> 00:59:11,872
- What? What is it?
- What? Why?

1046
00:59:11,872 --> 00:59:12,872
Imagination is free, after all.

1047
00:59:12,872 --> 00:59:14,853
Hey, Kim Tak Soo!

1048
00:59:14,853 --> 00:59:16,972
[Taehan Liquor in-house
beer brand contest awards ceremony]

1049
00:59:16,972 --> 00:59:18,272
Thank you for waiting.

1050
00:59:18,272 --> 00:59:19,305
Then, starting now,

1051
00:59:19,305 --> 00:59:25,061
we'll begin the Taehan Liquor contest
awards ceremony to find the next Try beer.

1052
00:59:27,138 --> 00:59:28,905
Thank you.

1053
00:59:28,905 --> 00:59:32,505
Taehan Liquor's President, Kang Du Jun,
will present the awards.

1054
00:59:32,505 --> 00:59:33,572
Please welcome him

1055
00:59:33,572 --> 00:59:35,772
with a big round of applause.

1056
00:59:38,138 --> 00:59:39,338
He's so handsome.

1057
00:59:39,338 --> 00:59:42,772
Kang Du Jun! Kang Du Jun!

1058
00:59:48,738 --> 00:59:50,305
Hello, I'm Kang Du Jun.

1059
00:59:50,305 --> 00:59:54,305
Thank you all for showing
so much interest in this contest.

1060
00:59:54,305 --> 00:59:57,672
Through this opportunity, I've been able to
feel the talent and passion of our employees,

1061
00:59:57,672 --> 01:00:00,638
and it's been a rewarding time
for me as well.

1062
01:00:00,638 --> 01:00:04,038
I will now announce the winners.

1063
01:00:08,677 --> 01:00:09,701
[3rd Place]

1064
01:00:10,338 --> 01:00:12,038
Third place.

1065
01:00:12,038 --> 01:00:13,669
Assistant Manager Choi Jong Seo
from the PR team.

1066
01:00:13,669 --> 01:00:15,605
Oh my, it's you!

1067
01:00:15,605 --> 01:00:18,205
Next, I'll announce second place.

1068
01:00:18,938 --> 01:00:21,872
Manager Kim Min Jae from the Sales Team.

1069
01:00:23,538 --> 01:00:25,125
[2nd Place]

1070
01:00:27,013 --> 01:00:28,773
[1st Place]

1071
01:00:30,738 --> 01:00:33,138
Now, only the long-awaited
first place remains.

1072
01:00:33,138 --> 01:00:38,105
The first prize will be 30 million won
and the chance to launch their own product.

1073
01:00:38,105 --> 01:00:41,805
Please announce the first-place winner.

1074
01:00:41,805 --> 01:00:45,338
Yes, I will announce first place.

1075
01:00:46,629 --> 01:00:50,085
[1st Place]

1076
01:00:54,372 --> 01:00:55,905
First place

1077
01:00:55,905 --> 01:00:58,072
goes to the New Product Development Team's

1078
01:00:59,238 --> 01:01:01,669
Manager Jang Hui Won, congratulations.

1079
01:01:04,517 --> 01:01:08,229
Congratulations! Congratulations!

1080
01:01:08,229 --> 01:01:10,085
Well done!

1081
01:01:13,829 --> 01:01:16,165
Good work!

1082
01:01:18,821 --> 01:01:20,197
[1st Place]

1083
01:01:22,005 --> 01:01:23,772
That's enough, that's enough.

1084
01:01:26,972 --> 01:01:28,705
Hold it!

1085
01:01:29,505 --> 01:01:32,638
I have an objection to the contest results.

1086
01:01:33,938 --> 01:01:37,172
I apologize, but during the judging process,

1087
01:01:37,172 --> 01:01:40,005
allegations have surfaced
that President Kang Du Jun

1088
01:01:40,005 --> 01:01:43,077
gave special treatment
to a specific participant.

1089
01:01:43,077 --> 01:01:44,438
- What?
- What is she saying?

1090
01:01:44,438 --> 01:01:46,638
That's absurd. In this judging process, I...

1091
01:01:46,638 --> 01:01:49,905
That female employee
President Kang Du Jun is seeing.

1092
01:01:49,905 --> 01:01:55,301
He deliberately gave
first place to that employee.

1093
01:01:55,301 --> 01:01:57,317
What?

1094
01:01:57,317 --> 01:02:00,272
- Oh, my.
- Is it real?

1095
01:02:00,272 --> 01:02:01,272
Du Jun.

1096
01:02:01,272 --> 01:02:05,838
No matter what, you should have
separated business from personal matters.

1097
01:02:07,872 --> 01:02:09,038
Don't you agree, sister-in-law?

1098
01:02:09,038 --> 01:02:12,261
- Sister-in-law?
- They're in-laws?

1099
01:02:12,261 --> 01:02:13,861
- What?
- No way!

1100
01:02:13,861 --> 01:02:15,605
- Jeez.
- How?

1101
01:02:15,605 --> 01:02:16,838
That woman is Manager Jang?

1102
01:02:16,838 --> 01:02:18,972
- Then...
- I mean they are...

1103
01:02:18,972 --> 01:02:20,872
The President and her...

1104
01:02:20,872 --> 01:02:23,237
Oh, my.

1105
01:02:25,509 --> 01:02:27,493
Goodness.

1106
01:02:41,538 --> 01:02:43,238
Watch out!

1107
01:02:50,341 --> 01:02:52,938
- What happened?
- It fell!

1108
01:02:52,938 --> 01:02:54,205
Is he hurt?

1109
01:02:54,205 --> 01:02:55,272
- Oh no!
- What do we do?

1110
01:02:55,272 --> 01:02:57,317
Call! Call 911!

1111
01:02:57,317 --> 01:02:58,373
I'm on it.

1112
01:02:58,373 --> 01:03:00,705
- Call them!
- Stay calm.

1113
01:03:51,205 --> 01:03:52,272
Will you be alright?

1114
01:03:52,272 --> 01:03:53,372
I feel relieved.

1115
01:03:53,372 --> 01:03:54,472
I have nothing to hide.

1116
01:03:54,472 --> 01:03:55,738
I heard she's even pregnant?

1117
01:03:55,738 --> 01:03:57,138
She's really something else.

1118
01:03:57,138 --> 01:04:00,105
I'm fine. The truth will come out eventually.

1119
01:04:00,105 --> 01:04:02,772
Do you know
she's putting together a new board?

1120
01:04:02,772 --> 01:04:03,905
Kang Du Jun!

1121
01:04:03,905 --> 01:04:07,138
Whether I received preferential treatment
or not is something you need to clarify.

1122
01:04:07,138 --> 01:04:08,272
Just pretend nothing happened.

1123
01:04:08,272 --> 01:04:10,205
I'll pin it on misconduct anyway.

1124
01:04:10,205 --> 01:04:11,333
Your name's right there

1125
01:04:11,333 --> 01:04:12,838
[Taehan Liquor in-house contest judge]
on the list of attendees.

1126
01:04:12,838 --> 01:04:15,205
And did the Vice Chairman say
he'd cover everything up again?

1127
01:04:15,205 --> 01:04:16,772
Should I greet first?

1128
01:04:16,772 --> 01:04:21,638
I'll make sure to lead
Taehan Liquor well, so don't worry.
